The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning for a robot to navigate in a non-static environment, which is a common topic in the robotics community (cs.RO). The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the artificial intelligence category (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of historical data to train the robot, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the integration of a model of the environment into the robot's motion control, which suggests that it may fall under the systems and control category (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of real-world ocean disturbances, which may suggest that it falls under the computer vision category (cs.CV) if the robot is using sensors to perceive the environment.
